# =============================================================================
# Terrascan rule skip list for ShopOS development environment
#
# Format: one Rule ID per line (comments with #)
# These rules are suppressed because they represent acceptable trade-offs
# in a development/staging environment and are addressed at the platform level.
#
# Review and remove these before production hardening.
# =============================================================================

# AWS.CloudWatch.Logging.Medium.0019
# Reason: CloudWatch detailed monitoring is not enabled on dev EC2 instances.
#         Monitoring is handled by Prometheus + Grafana at the application layer.
#         Acceptable for dev; enforce in prod via Terraform workspace condition.
AWS.CloudWatch.Logging.Medium.0019

# AC-K8-NS-PO-H-0002
# Reason: Pod Security Admission (PSA) 'restricted' profile blocks some
#         infrastructure pods (Vault agent injector, Falco DaemonSet) that
#         require elevated capabilities. These are reviewed manually and
#         controlled via Kyverno namespace-level exemptions.
AC-K8-NS-PO-H-0002

# AC-K8-NS-PO-M-0308
# Reason: Default service account tokens are auto-mounted in some namespaces
#         for internal tooling (Argo Workflows, Backstage). Addressed by
#         setting automountServiceAccountToken: false per-pod in production.
AC-K8-NS-PO-M-0308

# AC-HLM-NS-IR-M-0004
# Reason: Some Helm charts lack resource limits on init containers (e.g., DB
#         migration init containers). These are short-lived and adding limits
#         introduces migration timeout risk. Will be addressed in Helm chart v2.
AC-HLM-NS-IR-M-0004

# AC-TRF-MON-CERT-M-0144
# Reason: Traefik TLS certificate expiry monitoring is handled by cert-manager
#         with automatic renewal (Let's Encrypt / Vault PKI). Terrascan flags
#         the absence of an explicit monitoring annotation, but the cert-manager
#         CertificateRequest controller handles rotation proactively.
AC-TRF-MON-CERT-M-0144
